                            <comment id="369997" author="adilger" created="Thu, 20 Apr 2023 03:39:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Alex, could you please push a patch to skip both test_151 and test_156 during interop testing.  There is already a helper function &lt;tt&gt;check_versions&lt;/tt&gt; that can be used for this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="369995" author="adilger" created="Thu, 20 Apr 2023 03:33:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since this is really testing server-side functionality only (OSS caching behavior) it makes sense to just exclude test_151 and test_156 during interop testing, otherwise it seems that the client version of the test can become inconsistent with the caching behavior/tunables on the OSS and the failures don&apos;t mean anything.  There is enough non-interop testing to catch any regressions in the OSS cache behavior.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
